A 27 year old lady, Hannatu Mohammed is on the board of Independent Corrupt Practises Commission (ICPC). This appointment is eliciting a lot of reactions on social media, especially with regard to her supposed inexperience. But interestingly, the ICPC Act requires that a young person below the age of 30 must be in that board before it is properly constituted. Section 3 of ICPC Act. See her CV as available on ICPC website. The act is also silent about the experience required. So, it is an appointment in order. The real question is why doesnâ€™t the law mandate on experience required. Anyway, see reactions below: